response.content:
The main coral reef system in the Florida Keys is known as the **Florida Reef**, which is the only living coral barrier reef in the continental United States. It stretches approximately 350 miles from the Dry Tortugas to the St. Lucie Inlet and is home to over 40 species of reef-building coral.

Unfortunately, I was unable to retrieve the weather conditions for early February in the Florida Keys. However, typically, February is a good time for diving in the Florida Keys, as the weather is generally mild and the water conditions are favorable.

For the most accurate and up-to-date weather information, I recommend checking a reliable weather website closer to your travel date.
